- Candidate 2 (Bright, guitar‑forward AOR): matches my top stated preference directly — guitar‑forward, bright AOR tonality. It explicitly offers dry, center‑front vocals with minimal reverb, preserved transients, crisp separation, punchy groove‑forward low end, and tight sequencing. Those are very close technical matches to my core desires (guitar focus, dry intimate lead, low compression/preserved dynamics, punchy mids, clear imaging). The one clear negative relative to my dislikes is the “stacked harmony choruses,” which can compete with a lead vocal; however the description also emphasizes mixes tailored for listeners who favour intimate, hook‑first, revealing mixes, which implies the lead remains forward even with harmonies. Overall, the candidate hits the most important sonic markers I prioritized: guitar prominence, dry centered leads, preserved dynamics, and revealing mix balance.
